# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:54
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_97b5882d:

    # "You are sitting by a campfire along with two girls."
    "Estás sentado junto a una fogata junto con dos chicas."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:56
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_fde24efd:

    # girl "When I got the first one, I was literally seconds away from stepping onto the plane when a call from “UNKNOWN” blared from my cell phone."
    girl "La primera vez, estaba literalmente a unos segundos de subir al avión cuando una llamada de “DESCONOCIDO” sonó desde mi teléfono celular."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:58
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_fb5f18ff:

    # girl "It was a ringtone I hadn’t heard before, one I was pretty sure hadn’t come with the phone."
    girl "Era un tono de llamada que no había escuchado antes, y estoy bastante segura de que no había venido con el teléfono."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:60
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e8840b80:

    # girl "Normally, I wouldn’t have stopped to answer it, but I was expecting a call about a job I had interviewed for the previous week."
    girl "Normalmente, no habría parado para responderla, pero esperaba una llamada sobre un trabajo por el que tuve una entrevista la semana anterior."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:62
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_21158a1b:

    # girl "I took a deep breath in and accepted the call."
    girl "Respiré hondo y acepté la llamada."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:64
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_73a24cd5:

    # girl "“Hello?”"
    girl "“¿Hola?”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:66
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1239fc0d:

    # girl "“Do not get on the plane.” A woman’s voice, garbled and strange, as if her vocal chords had been shredded, and she was trying desperately to choke out speech."
    girl "No subas al avión.” La voz de una mujer, distorsionada y extraña, como si sus cuerdas vocales se hubieran hecho trizas, y estuviera tratando desesperadamente de hablar mientras se ahogaba."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:68
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_54de4487:

    # girl "Despite the unnerving, fractured quality of her voice, her tone was insistent and eerily calm. Then the call ended."
    girl "A pesar de lo desconcertante de su fracturada voz, su tono era insistente y extrañamente tranquilo. Y la llamada terminó."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:70
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d698489f:

    # girl "I froze. I had always had a slight phobia of air travel, and something about this call just… there’s no way I was about to get on a seven hour flight now."
    girl "Me quedé paralizada. Siempre había tenido una ligera fobia a los viajes aéreos, y algo acerca de esta llamada simplemente... no había forma de que vaya a tomar un vuelo de siete horas ahora."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:72
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_421b7851:

    # girl "I turned around and headed toward the food court. I’d just get another flight later in the afternoon, I figured."
    girl "Me di la vuelta y me dirigí hacia el patio de comidas. Me imaginé que tomaría otro vuelo en la tarde."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:74
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_63a886ce:

    # girl "I watched from the airport Starbucks three hours later as every TV in the terminal lit up with the crash footage of the plane I should have been on."
    girl "Tres horas más tarde, vi desde el Starbucks en el aeropuerto en todos los televisores de la terminal se iluminaban con las imágenes del accidente del avión en el que debería haber estado."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:76
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bc7f4c61:

    # girl "No survivors. Not a single one."
    girl "Sin sobrevivientes. Ni uno sólo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:78
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_ab2ced9c:

    # girl "I tried to trace the call. So did the police. But there was nothing to trace."
    girl "Traté de rastrear la llamada. También lo hizo la policía. Pero no había nada que rastrear."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:80
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bd51ca37:

    # girl "There was no evidence my phone had ever received a call around that time."
    girl "No había evidencia de que mi teléfono hubiera recibido una llamada en ese momento."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:82
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_37a98374:

    # girl "They analyzed phone records, incoming and outgoing communication to my phone… nothing."
    girl "Analizaron registros telefónicos, comunicaciones entrantes y salientes a mi teléfono… nada."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:84
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f12f50a0:

    # girl "I wasn’t making it up. I couldn’t have been."
    girl "No me lo estaba inventando. No podría haberlo hecho."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:86
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b62b5aff:

    # girl "That wasn’t the only call. Throughout the years, they were few and far between, but always right. And I always listened."
    girl "Ésa no fue la única llamada. A lo largo de los años, fueron pocos y espaciados, pero siempre acertaron. Y siempre escuché."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:88
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1877f646:

    # girl "“Do not go on that blind date tonight.”"
    girl "“No vayas a esa cita a ciegas esta noche.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:90
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_8c176096:

    # girl "Five months later, my would-be “date” was convicted of killing four women, all with my hair color and build."
    girl "Cinco meses después, mi posible “cita” fue condenado por matar a cuatro mujeres, todas con mi color de cabello y constitución."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:92
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d10f4704:

    # girl "Found them in a shallow grave about 250 feet from the diner he offered to take me to."
    girl "Las encontraron en una tumba poco profunda a unos 250 pies del restaurante al que se ofreció a llevarme."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:94
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e86aaae5:

    # girl "“Do not drive to the concert tonight.”"
    girl "“No conduzcas al concierto esta noche.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:96
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_8cbb51df:

    # girl "Eighteen-wheeler lost control and plowed into a line of cars. Every driver crushed. Every driver killed. In the stretch of freeway I would have been driving down."
    girl "El camión de dieciocho ruedas perdió el control y se estrelló contra una línea de autos. Cada conductor chocó. Cada conductor murió. Yo habría estado conduciendo ahí, en el tramo de la autopista."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:98
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_90eaa6d9:

    # girl "No matter if I got a new phone, if I moved across the country, the calls would still come."
    girl "No importa si tengo un teléfono nuevo, o si me mudo al otro lado del país, las llamadas seguirán llegando."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:100
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2d667a79:

    # girl "I could almost feel the presence of… whatever it was, whatever it is, watching over me."
    girl "Casi podía sentir la presencia de... lo que fuera, lo que sea, cuidándome."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:102
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e2d6148c:

    # girl "I imagined being at the bottom of the freezing ocean, still strapped into my coach-section plane seat, or being in that mass grave across from the diner, or watching an eighteen-wheeler skidding toward my car, knowing death was imminent, and I’d get this tightness in my chest."
    girl "Me imaginé estar en el fondo del océano helado, todavía atada a mi asiento del avión de la sección de clase turista, o estar en esa fosa común frente al restaurante, o ver un camión de dieciocho ruedas patinando hacia mi auto, sabiendo que la muerte era inminente , y sentiría esta opresión en mi pecho."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:104
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_95106561:

    # girl "I’d think about how thin that line was. How close I’d gotten."
    girl "Pensaría en lo delgada que era esa línea. Lo cerca que había estado."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:106
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1e741921:

    # girl "If I hadn’t had a job interview I was waiting to hear back from, I’d have never listened to that first call. And that would be it for me."
    girl "Si no hubiera tenido una entrevista de trabajo de la que esperaba noticias, nunca hubiera escuchado esa primera llamada. Y eso hubiera sido todo para mi."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:108
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2496f8d6:

    # girl "It always felt like something was coming for me. But there was always this… this fractured, warped voice, with these calls that never seemed to exist after I heard them."
    girl "Siempre sentí que algo venía por mí. Pero siempre estaba esta... esta voz rota y deformada, con estas llamadas que nunca parecían existir después de que las recibí."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:110
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_171217b0:

    # girl "Self-destructing warning signals, rotting away before my eyes. And I was alive."
    girl "Señales de advertencia autodestructivas, pudriéndose ante mis ojos. Y yo estaba viva."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:112
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_dd5b80c2:

    # girl "I had a bad feeling about this cruise."
    girl "Tenía un mal presentimiento sobre este crucero."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:114
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2193857a:

    # girl "I had planned it as a girl’s week out with some of my old friends from college, and was looking forward to a week in the tropics in the dead of winter—but part of me could almost sense that the call was coming."
    girl "Lo había planeado como una semana de las chicas con algunas de mis viejas amigas de la universidad, y estaba deseando pasar una semana en los trópicos al final del invierno, pero una parte de mí casi podía sentir que llegaba la llamada."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:116
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2e6284a5:

    # girl "Maybe I’d watched Titanic one too many times, but there was a little nagging fear from the start."
    girl "Quizás había visto Titanic demasiadas veces, pero había un poco de miedo persistente desde el principio."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:118
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c8d4677a:

    # girl "I hoped it would be fine, but I knew that if something was going to happen, I’d get the call. I’d know."
    girl "Esperaba que todo estuviera bien, pero sabía que si algo iba a pasar, recibiría la llamada. Lo sabría."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:120
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_ddb7e37c:

    # girl "Now, a week before I’m set to go on the cruise, after stepping into my apartment after returning from dinner with a friend, I notice my cell has a message from “UNKNOWN”."
    girl "Ahora, una semana antes de que esté listo para viajar en el crucero, después de entrar en mi apartamento al regresar de cenar con un amigo, noto que mi celular tiene un mensaje de “DESCONOCIDO”."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:122
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_ea09be3f:

    # girl "They’ve never had to leave a message before. Haven’t checked it all night."
    girl "Nunca antes habían tenido que dejar un mensaje. No lo había revisado en toda la noche."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:124
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_8304e183:

    # girl "Damn it, and I had really wanted to go on that cruise, too."
    girl "Maldita sea, y yo que también tenía muchas ganas de ir en ese crucero."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:126
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c576140e:

    # girl "Ah, well. Not worth whatever horrific fate awaited me in that cold dark ocean."
    girl "Ah, bueno. No vale la pena el horrible destino que me aguardaba en ese frío océano oscuro."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:128
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_04f2ef02:

    # girl "I click “play message”, and feel my stomach drop as I listen to the voice, sounding horrifically distorted, as if it emanates from a throat slashed to ribbons, crackling with more urgency than ever before."
    girl "Hago clic en “reproducir mensaje” y siento que se me cae el estómago al escuchar la voz, que suena horriblemente distorsionada, como si emanara de una garganta cortada en cintas, crujiendo con más urgencia que nunca."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:130
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bfb9bd27:

    # girl "I look around my apartment as the voice on the phone repeats the same phrase over and over again."
    girl "Miro alrededor de mi apartamento mientras la voz del teléfono repite la misma frase una y otra vez."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:132
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b2f54aa3:

    # girl "“Do not come home after dinner tonight. Do not come home after dinner tonight. DO NOT COME HOME AFTER DINNER TONIGHT.”"
    girl "“No vengas a casa después de cenar esta noche. No vengas a casa después de cenar esta noche. NO VENGAS A CASA DESPUÉS DE CENAR ESTA NOCHE.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:137
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ac660d1:

    # "They suddenly turn towards you. Their mouth turned up into a warm grin. Their eyes sinister."
    "De repente miran en tu dirección. Sus bocas forman en una cálida sonrisa. Sus ojos siniestros."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_17070b3b:

    # man "Over the hill and through the moor, the candle man comes walking, up to your door."
    man "Sobre la colina y atravesando el páramo, el candelero viene caminando, hasta tu puerta."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_6e1bb453:

    # man "He lights up a candle and walks to your bed, leaves the candle in the window, and leaves with your head."
    man "El enciende una vela y camina hacia tu cama, deja la vela en la ventana y se va con tu cabeza."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a41d7737:

    # man "That’s the nursery rhyme my grandma used to tell me when I was young."
    man "Esa es la canción de cuna que solía contarme mi abuela cuando era joven."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c4756094:

    # man "I remember that little rhyme terrifying me as a child, as I cowered under the covers in the bed at her small country cottage, too scared to sleep."
    man "Recuerdo esa pequeña rima que me aterrorizaba cuando era un niño, mientras me acurrucaba debajo de las sábanas en la cama de su pequeña casa de campo, demasiado asustado para dormir."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_85096136:

    # man "She described him as a tall, pale man in a robe, who liked to kill little children."
    man "Ella lo describió como un hombre alto y pálido con una túnica, al que le gustaba matar niños pequeños."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_6e86fd7f:

    # man "“And whenever he killed,” Grandma would say in hushed voice ‘he would leave a ghostly candle in their window” at that she would yell out and make me jump back in fright while she shrieked with laughter."
    man "“Y cuando sea que mate,” decía la Abuela en voz baja ‘dejaba una vela fantasmal en su ventana” y entonces gritaría y me haría saltar asustado, mientras ella chillaba de la risa."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_56c7ca18:

    # man "“The candle man”, even the name gives me chills."
    man "“El hombre de la vela”, incluso el nombre me da escalofríos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b405661e:

    # man "It seemed like such a horrible, scary thing to say to a child, but then again, Grandma was a scary woman."
    man "Parecía algo demasiado horrible y aterrador para contarle a un niño, pero, de nuevo, la abuela era una mujer aterradora."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_6146bf35:

    # man "She was small, with weathered skin and cruel, sunken eyes that always seemed to glare at me."
    man "She was small, with weathered skin and cruel, sunken eyes that always seemed to glare at me."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d70f7e77:

    # man "After Grandpa died she hardly ever left her house, just sat in her rocking chair, telling stories of the candle man and taking delight in my fear, laughing madly when I jumped. I found her such a disgusting woman."
    man "After Grandpa died she hardly ever left her house, just sat in her rocking chair, telling stories of the candle man and taking delight in my fear, laughing madly when I jumped. I found her such a disgusting woman."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_05a644e5:

    # man "Anyway, when grew up, I learned that it wasn’t her fault really, Grandpa’s death had shaken her up, messed with her head."
    man "De todos modos, cuando crecí, supe que en realidad no era culpa suya. La muerte del Abuelo la había sacudido, estropeadole la cabeza."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c208c0e0:

    # man "She didn’t know what was appropriate anymore."
    man "Ya no sabía lo que era apropiado."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_41c83bbd:

    # man "Grandpa was only alive when I was a baby and I never knew him, but I learned when I was older how much he had meant to Grandma."
    man "El Abuelo vivió cuando yo era un bebé y nunca lo conocí, pero cuando fui mayor supe lo mucho que significaba para la Abuela."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e59152ca:

    # man "Without him, she had been broken."
    man "Sin el, ella se había roto."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_474869af:

    # man "She died when I was thirteen, and I guess it didn’t really come to me as much of a shock, she was incredibly old and frail."
    man "Murió cuando yo tenía trece años, y supongo que no me sorprendió tanto, ya que era increíblemente vieja y frágil."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_74b63845:

    # man "Now I’m thirty, with a wife and a little girl. We have a comfortable suburban home, and I couldn’t be happier."
    man "Ahora tengo treinta años, con una esposa y una niña. Tenemos una buena casa en los suburbios y no podría estar más feliz."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_50040345:

    # man "There has been one thing that’s shaken me up recently, however."
    man "Sin embargo, hubo algo que me ha preocupado."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b7e161e2:

    # man "It was a silly thing, but it still scared the hell out of me."
    man "Fue una tontería, pero aun así me asustó muchísimo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_fc60421b:

    # man "A nightmare."
    man "Una pesadilla."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_7c02afa4:

    # man "In the dream I was in my bedroom, comfy under the covers, when I heard a tune being played on the piano downstairs."
    man "En el sueño estaba en mi habitación, cómodo bajo las sábanas, cuando escuché una melodía en el piano de abajo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_443fe769:

    # man "I knew what was being played as soon as I heard it, “the candle man”."
    man "Supe lo que se estaba reproduciendo tan pronto como lo escuché, “el hombre de la vela”."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_50ffd746:

    # man "Goosebumps ran up my arms and neck, and ice filled my stomach."
    man "Sentí escalofríos en mis brazos y cuello, y como si mi estómago se helara."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a9186c78:

    # man "I sprinted down the narrow staircase into the living room, where I saw a tall, pale figure in a robe holding a candle, leaving through the open door."
    man "Corrí por la estrecha escalera hacia la sala de estar, donde vi una figura, alta y pálida, envuelto en una túnica y sosteniendo una vela, saliendo por la puerta abierta."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c8d018e1:

    # man "The candle man. He was about six foot four or five, with dead looking beady eyes and a wide, evil grin."
    man "El hombre de la vela. Medía un metro ochenta o más, tenía unos ojos pequeños y brillantes, y una amplia y malvada sonrisa."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_3305245e:

    # man "I woke up suddenly in a cold sweat, turned on the light, and read until I was ready to sleep again."
    man "Me desperté repentinamente con un sudor frío, encendí la luz y leí hasta que estuve listo para dormir de nuevo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_45f9bc32:

    # man "I put the dream down to too many drinks and the coming of Halloween, but it freaked me out anyway."
    man "Atribuí el sueño a demasiadas bebidas y la llegada de Halloween, pero de todos modos me asustó."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ed10514:

    # man "And that takes me up to yesterday, Halloween night."
    man "Y eso me lleva hasta ayer, la noche de Halloween."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f70eeb03:

    # man "I was trudging back from a party, not drunk, (I don’t drink) but still woozy from tiredness."
    man "Estaba regresando de una fiesta, no borracho, pero todavía mareado por el cansancio."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_716e9ad4:

    # man "I thrust my hands into my pockets for warmth."
    man "Me meto las manos en los bolsillos para calentarme."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_44ebb6c3:

    # man "Whilst I was walking back through the crisp orange leaves, the poem of the candle man popped into my head."
    man "Mientras caminaba de regreso a través de las frescas hojas de naranja, el poema del hombre de la vela apareció en mi cabeza."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_5c2186a4:

    # man "My heart began to thud as I walked down the poorly-lit street, leaves crunching underfoot, the pale moon casting long shadows along the path."
    man "Mi corazón comenzó a latir con fuerza mientras caminaba por la calle mal iluminada, las hojas aplastándose bajo mis pies, la luna pálida proyectaba largas sombras a lo largo del camino."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f64a422f:

    # man "In my mind’s eye, I could see the candle man, thin and ghostly, running up to me and cutting off my head in one swing of an axe."
    man "En mi mente, pude ver al hombre de la vela, delgado y fantasmal, corriendo hacia mí y cortándome la cabeza con un hacha."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_5dd15dc0:

    # man "Silly I know, but the dark can make my imagination run wild sometimes."
    man "Tonto, lo sé, pero a veces la oscuridad puede volver loca a la imaginación."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e7ad3e13:

    # man "I arrived on my road and began to calm down."
    man "Llegué al camino hacia mi casa y comencé a calmarme."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_735359a5:

    # man "I felt silly for having let the poem get to me."
    man "Me sentí tonto por haber dejado que el poema me afectara."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_016860e5:

    # man "I was perfectly safe under the streetlights."
    man "Estaba perfectamente a salvo bajo las luces de la calle."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a7b2f941:

    # man "As I arrived at my front yard, I noticed a tall man in a robe standing at the end of the street, his face shrouded in darkness."
    man "Cuando llegué al frente de mi casa, noté a un hombre alto con una túnica de pie al final de la calle, con el rostro envuelto en la oscuridad."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_ebd89e61:

    # man "He appeared to be staring at me."
    man "Parecía que me miraba fijamente."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c07f7fd2:

    # man "Once again images of the candle man flooded through my head, sending my heartbeat into overdrive."
    man "Una vez más, las imágenes del hombre de la vela llenaron mi cabeza, haciendo que mi corazón acelerara sin parar."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1ca9d7ef:

    # man "I shook it off."
    man "Decidí ignorarlo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:149
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d7bec823:

    # man "“It’s just a tall man out for Halloween, nothing to be scared of,” I assured myself, as I attempted to slow my breathing."
    man "“Es solo un hombre alto vestido para Halloween, nada a lo que tenerle miedo,” pensaba para asegurarme, y traté de desacelerar mi respiración."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:239
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e7d11049:

    # man "Then I looked up at my house, hearing demonic laughter from the man’s direction."
    man "Luego miré hacia mi casa, escuchando una risa demoníaca proveniente del hombre."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:240
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2999497f:

    # man "An icicle of terror stabbed at my heart."
    man "Sentí como si hielo me apuñalara en el corazón."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:244
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d608c514:

    # man "There, in my daughter’s window, flickering softly, was a candle."
    man "Allí, en la ventana de mi hija, parpadeando suavemente, había una vela."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:249
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ac660d1_1:

    # "They suddenly turn towards you. Their mouth turned up into a warm grin. Their eyes sinister."
    "De repente miran en tu dirección. Sus bocas forman en una cálida sonrisa. Sus ojos siniestros."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1bea3c92:

    # man "You are taking a shower."
    man "Estás tomando una ducha."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d68c5057:

    # man "It’s not the type of shower you take before a job interview, maybe aiming for your cleanliness to impress somebody or someone supposedly worthy of impressing, nor is it the type of shower you take after a long workout at the gym or after a jog, or after whatever it is that applies to you."
    man "No del tipo que tomas antes de una entrevista de trabajo, con el objetivo de que tal vez tu limpieza impresione a alguien supuestamente digno de impresionar, ni es el tipo de ducha que tomas después de un largo entrenamiento en el gimnasio o después de correr, o después de lo que sea que se aplique a ti."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c23f74e5:

    # man "No, you’re in your bathroom right now, standing under the soothing beam of hot water with wisps of steam spiraling off of your back."
    man "No, estás en tu baño en este momento, bajo la relajante agua caliente y con algo de vapor emanando de tu espalda."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_017fd8c9:

    # man "Because you’ve got nothing better to do tonight, and you like that squeaky-clean feeling before hitting the hay, and, although this isn’t your first shower today, at least you can sleep easy knowing you’re cleansed of the day’s many stresses."
    man "Ya que no tienes nada mejor que hacer esta noche, y te gusta esa sensación de limpieza antes de ir a dormir, y, aunque esta no es su primera ducha hoy, al menos puedes dormir tranquilo sabiendo que estás libre de las muchas tensiones del día."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_35e7c9f6:

    # man "Soap."
    man "Jabón."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_cbe6a3d7:

    # man "Shampoo."
    man "Shampoo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e770d66c:

    # man "It’s all there, but you don’t so much as touch it."
    man "Están ahí, pero ni siquiera los tocas."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e5c7e12e:

    # man "For now you’re just letting the water’s steam filter through your pores, and enjoying the simplicity of it all."
    man "Por ahora, solo estás dejando que el vapor del agua se filtre a través de tus poros y disfrutando su simplicidad."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_0e3e5b8a:

    # man "The lights go out."
    man "Las luces se van."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b86c1a6a:

    # man "Startled, your feet squeal on the floor of the shower and you pause to make sure the sound was from your own."
    man "Asustado, tus pies chillan en el piso de la ducha y haces una pausa para asegurarte de que el sonido provino de ti."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e182d824:

    # man "The sound of water hitting the floor in the dark."
    man "El sonido del agua golpeando el piso en la oscuridad."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_18e8008b:

    # man "You feel as if you’re not alone in the room. Which is impossible, because you’re the only one in the house."
    man "Sientes como si no estuvieras solo en la habitación. Lo cual es imposible, porque eres el único en la casa ."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_40979a4e:

    # man "The sound of the switch had been unmistakable."
    man "El sonido del interruptor había sido inconfundible ."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_31674d6e:

    # man "You stay under it, under the water, your one and only landmark."
    man "Te quedas debajo de la ducha, debajo del agua, tu único punto de referencia."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_232b6ba5:

    # man "Feeling around, your hands meet the slippery shower tiles, and you feel like a mime trapped in a blank box as you fumble for the adjacent wall, then grab the curtain, finally something real, something you can touch that’s now in front of you and will stay static as you reclaim your bearings."
    man "Palpando a tu alrededor, tus manos se encuentran con los resbaladizos azulejos de la ducha y te sientes como un mimo atrapado en una caja mientras buscas a tientas la pared adyacente, y agarras la cortina. Finalmente algo real, algo que puedes tocar que ahora está enfrente y permanecerá estático mientras te recuperas."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a83f57e7:

    # man "Outside of the shower, something starts choking."
    man "Fuera de la ducha, algo comienza a asfixiarse."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_904d6b3d:

    # man "You abruptly stop breathing. Strain to hear."
    man "Dejas de respirar abruptamente. Te esfuerzas por oír."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a1cb5b19:

    # man "It’s a gut-wrenching cough that wheezes in and out, and your hand freezes before recoiling back to your torso in shock."
    man "Es una tos desgarradora que entra y sale, y tu mano se congela antes de retroceder hacia tu torso en estado de shock."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f410a257:

    # man "And in the middle of the bathwater rain noisily splashing by your feet, you hear its footsteps inching closer as it struggles to breathe."
    man "Y en medio del agua del baño cayendo, salpicando ruidosamente a tus pies, oyes sus pasos acercándose poco a poco mientras lucha por respirar."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c37b6dfd:

    # man "The thump of pads on the floor stepping closer."
    man "El golpe desde la alfombra en el suelo, acercándose."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_90cdb521:

    # man "You can do nothing but press your back against the wet wall behind you in paralysis, to the point where the sounds are less than a foot away from where you remember the curtain to be, at your own eye level."
    man "No puedes hacer nada más que presionar tu espalda contra la pared húmeda detrás de ti, paralizado, hasta el punto en que los sonidos están a menos de un pie de distancia de donde recuerdas que está la cortina, a la altura de tus ojos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1d02148d:

    # man "That’s when the lights come on and the choking stops."
    man "Ahí es cuando se encienden las luces y se detienen los sonidos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f9c132b6:

    # man "You shut off the water."
    man "Cierras el agua."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d4f81874:

    # man "All is quiet and you look to either side just in case, remembering all the horror movies you’ve seen in your entire life at this moment."
    man "Todo está en silencio y miras a ambos lados por si acaso, recordando en este momento todas las películas de terror que has visto en tu vida."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_8f850bd1:

    # man "Not a sound except the gurgling of the drain at your toes, sucking down the last of the water calmly like it had all been in your head and none of it had happened."
    man "Ni un sonido, excepto el gorgoteo del desagüe en los dedos de tus pies, succionando lo último del agua con calma como si todo hubiera estado en tu cabeza y nada hubiera sucedido."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:263
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_14501f3e:

    # man "You’re standing there, dripping wet and naked, when you realize you’ve got to step out and meet whatever’s there, waiting on the other side of the curtain."
    man "Estás ahí parado, empapado y desnudo, cuando te das cuenta de que tienes que salir y encontrarte con lo que sea que esté allí, esperando al otro lado de la cortina."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:321
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ac660d1_2:

    # "They suddenly turn towards you. Their mouth turned up into a warm grin. Their eyes sinister."
    "De repente miran en tu dirección. Sus bocas forman en una cálida sonrisa. Sus ojos siniestros."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_9ec23ab7:

    # girl "It was hardly past seven that morning when the Gravedigger saw the Earth stir. Fingers, rotted and skeletal, burst forth from the dirt, and with force they pulled their bodies to freedom."
    girl "Apenas eran las siete de la mañana cuando el sepulturero vio que la Tierra se agitaba. Dedos podridos y esqueléticos brotaron de la tierra, y con fuerza sacaron sus cuerpos a la libertad."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f467aeb8:

    # girl "It was happening all over the graveyard. Every grave. Every square inch of dirt was overturned."
    girl "Estaba sucediendo en todo el cementerio. Cada tumba. Cada centímetro cuadrado de tierra fue volcado."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_004a140a:

    # girl "Soon, there were thousands; so many more than the graveyard actually held. A horde of the undead stood before him."
    girl "Pronto, había miles; Muchos mas de lo que el cementerio tenía. Una horda de no-muertos estaba frente a él."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_69cb1a78:

    # girl "The Gravedigger watched, with his shovel in hand."
    girl "El Sepulturero miraba, con su pala en mano."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_8f33bf24:

    # girl "He found himself simultaneously horrified and fascinated. The creatures stumbled about. They moved with urgency, but their decrepit bodies only allowed for so much. Yelling and screaming, they started to coalesce near the center of the graveyard."
    girl "Se encontró horrorizado y fascinado al mismo tiempo. Las criaturas tambaleaban. Se movían con urgencia, pero sus cuerpos decrépitos solo lo permitían hasta cierto punto. Gritando y chillando, comenzaron a juntarse cerca del centro del cementerio."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_8f4b8705:

    # girl "They were revolting, damned souls."
    girl "Eran almas repugnantes, malditas."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_05d07300:

    # girl "Just as the Gravedigger went to turn, to flee, a hand gripped his shoulder. The grime soaked deep into his sleeve. It leaked down his arm."
    girl "Justo cuando el Sepulturero iba a darse la vuelta, a huir, una mano lo agarró por el hombro. La mugre empapó profundamente su manga. Se deslizó por su brazo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1945723e:

    # girl "Behind him, a man (what was left of him) stared into the Gravedigger’s eyes. The corpse’s face had long since lost its tissue, but it had eyes, returned anew to their sockets, that showed nothing but fear."
    girl "Detrás de él, un hombre (lo que quedaba de él) lo miró a los ojos fijamente. El rostro del cadáver había perdido su tejido desde hacía mucho tiempo, pero tenía ojos, que volvieron de nuevo a sus órbitas, mostrando nada más que miedo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_48b823e1:

    # girl "The ghoul spoke to the Gravedigger, and the Gravedigger listened."
    girl "El ghoul le habló al Sepulturero, y el Sepulturero escuchó."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f39b8f60:

    # girl "“Go,” It begged of him. “Please. Go.”"
    girl "“Vé” le rogó. “Por favor. Vé.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4f05502f:

    # girl "What sort of madness was this? What trickery of Hell?"
    girl "¿Qué clase de locura era ésta? ¿Una trampa del Infierno?"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e9a2c332:

    # girl "The Gravedigger brought his shovel to bear, and he swung it down on the corpse. It was met with a revolting, moist crunch. The figure fell. His fingers twitched, and his skull leaked."
    girl "El Sepulturero alzó su pala, y la balanceó sobre el cadáver. Se encontró con un crujido repugnante y húmedo. La figura cayó. Sus dedos se retorcieron y su fluídos escapaban de su cráneo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_26c96823:

    # girl "From behind, three more figures came. Two ignored the Gravedigger. They bent to pick up the wounded husk at the Gravedigger’s feet."
    girl "Otras tres figuras vieneron desde atrás. Dos ignoraron al Sepulturero. Se inclinaron a sus pies para recoger lo que quedaba del cuerpo herido."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d26c892e:

    # girl "They dragged him on with all the strength they could muster. They carried him like a wounded ally. The third figure, what had once been a woman, perhaps, spoke to the Gravedigger."
    girl "Lo arrastraron con todas las fuerzas que pudieron reunir. Lo llevaron como un aliado herido. La tercera figura, la que quizás había sido una mujer, le habló al sepulturero."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1cbb68d3:

    # girl "She pleaded."
    girl "Ella suplicó."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_3d10c809:

    # girl "“Go. Please. Tell them.”"
    girl "“Vé. Por favor. Díles.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_389b7f97:

    # girl "The Gravedigger couldn’t move. He wouldn’t."
    girl "El Sepulturero no se movía. No podía."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d2308b1c:

    # girl "These fiends were no masters of him. Why did they command him so? For what purpose? Answers! He demanded answers!"
    girl "Estos demonios no eran amos de él. ¿Por qué le ordenaron ésto? ¿Con qué propósito? ¡Respuestas! ¡Exigió respuestas!"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_9636421a:

    # girl "“Why?” he asked, the words falling out of his bearded face. “Why aren’t you in the ground?”"
    girl "“¿Por qué?” preguntó, las palabras escapando de su boca barbuda. “¿Por qué no estás en la tierra?”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_27a1db80:

    # girl "The ghoul didn’t blink. She simply told him the terrible truth."
    girl "El ghoul ni siquiera pestañó. Ella simplemente le dijo la horrible verdad."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_9c760cc0:

    # girl "“Hell isn’t safe anymore.”"
    girl "“El Infierno ya no es seguro.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_71ce8887:

    # girl "Those words. The Gravedigger couldn’t even comprehend them. What was the meaning of them?"
    girl "Esas palabras. El Sepulturero no podía siquiera comprenderlas. ¿Que significaba ésto?"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_12d6eee2:

    # girl "Hell? Safe? What kind of haven was the pit of eternal damnation?"
    girl "¿Infierno? ¿Seguro? ¿Qué tipo de refugio era el pozo de la condenación eterna?"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b9974868:

    # girl "“What are you talking about?”"
    girl "“¿De qué estás hablando?”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2edd16ff:

    # girl "Had she a tear to cry she would have let it fall. Instead, she had to use her trembling voice to convey her fears."
    girl "Habría tenido una lágrima para derramar, ella la habría dejado caer. En cambio, tuvo que usar su voz temblorosa para transmitir sus miedos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e17f8ce4:

    # girl "“Lucifer is dead. He killed Him. He is coming.”"
    girl "Lucifer está muerto. Él lo mató. Él viene.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_445824a0:

    # girl "The words held no meaning for the Gravedigger, for he had not been there. He had not seen the horrors that even the denizens of Hell itself couldn’t describe."
    girl "Las palabras no tenían ningún significado para el Sepulturero, pues él no había estado allí. No había visto los horrores que incluso los habitantes del Infierno mismo no podían describir."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_61cfe24a:

    # girl "Then, from the graves, dark figures with eyes of flame and hatred came. They moved like smoke, and they filled the air with their sulfurous fumes."
    girl "Entonces, de las tumbas, salieron figuras oscuras con ojos de fuego y odio. Se movieron como el humo, y llenaron el aire con sus vapores sulfurosos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_d3a361d1:

    # girl "The Gravedigger watched as demons, Satan’s orchestrators of pain and suffering, began to assist the poor, wandering souls below."
    girl "El Sepulturero observó cómo los demonios, orquestadores del dolor y el sufrimiento elegidos por Satanás, comenzaban a ayudar a las pobres almas errantes de abajo."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_b7298132:

    # girl "They started to stack atop each other. One by one, their bodies built the foundation."
    girl "Comenzaron a apilarse unos sobre otros. Uno por uno, sus cuerpos establecieron una base."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1ce0205a:

    # girl "What in the name of God? He could only ponder."
    girl "¿Qué, en el nombre de Dios, es ésto? El solo podía preguntarse."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_57a041a9:

    # girl "A collective lamenting cascaded down from the hills around. The Gravedigger saw them."
    girl "Un lamento colectivo cayó en cascada desde las colinas circundantes. El Sepulturero los vió."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_6b74c567:

    # girl "From every direction more hordes moved together. More undead. They lumbered forth, with his cemetery in their sights. Their hellish rendezvous."
    girl "De toda dirección se movieron más hordas juntas. Más no-muertos. Avanzaron de a poco, con su cementerio en la mira. A su reunión infernal."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_0c0ce442:

    # girl "The Gravedigger was speechless."
    girl "El Sepulturero se quedó sin habla."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_de1658a4:

    # girl "The ghoul instructed him."
    girl "El ghoul lo instruyó."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_cd1eb694:

    # girl "“Go. To your family. We’ll need them too.”"
    girl "“Ve. A tu familia. Los necesitaremos también.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c1b1731f:

    # girl "“My—” he questioned the request, “My family?”"
    girl "“Mi—” cuestionándola, “Mi familia?”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_ebc3c19d:

    # girl "“The living,” the thing corrected, her gaze skyward. “We’ll need them too, if we are to make it.”"
    girl "“Los vivos,” la cosa corrigió, su mirada hacia el cielo. “Los necesitaremos también, si queremos sobrevivir.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c5b2870e:

    # girl "“Make it? Where?”"
    girl "“¿Sobrevivir? ¿Sobrevivir qué?”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_0cd608b7:

    # girl "The ghoul cried as she wandered forth. Urgency flooded her words."
    girl "El ghoul gritó mientras se alejaba. La urgencia inundó sus palabras."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_2fa41815:

    # girl "“The gates! We have to make it to the gates.”"
    girl "“¡Las puertas! Tenemos que llegar a las puertas.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_36f4fa19:

    # girl "The Gravedigger shook his head. Their aim was clear, but his teachings were concrete."
    girl "El Sepulturero negó con la cabeza. El objetivo era claro, pero sus propias enseñanzas eran concretas."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bc821e84:

    # girl "“What’s judged is judged. He won’t take you, or any of us unworthy.”"
    girl "“Lo que se juzga, está juzgado. No los tomará, ni a ninguno de nosotros los indignos.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_5e732d48:

    # girl "That stopped her, if for just a moment. She turned, for he knew nothing."
    girl "Eso la detuvo, aunque sólo sea por un momento. Se volvió, pues él no sabía nada."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ef33908:

    # girl "“We seek not redemption,” she said. “We damned seek to warn the righteous.”"
    girl "“No buscamos redemción,” ella dijo. “Los condenados queremos advertir a los justos.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_5d57870a:

    # girl "The honesty in the ghoul’s voice brought a heavy weight to the Gravedigger’s stomach."
    girl "La honestidad en la voz del ghoul le dio un gran peso al estómago del Sepulturero."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_31a0696f:

    # girl "He couldn’t stand. The Earth below had started to tremble."
    girl "De repente no pudo quedarse de pie. La tierra de abajo había comenzado a temblar."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_ded48d40:

    # girl "The Gravedigger fell to the dirt as his knees gave in, and with his face to the ground, he heard it."
    girl "El Sepulturero cayó al suelo cuando sus rodillas cedieron, y con la cara al suelo, lo escuchó."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_12b4d4bd:

    # girl "There was a deep, unbridled scream echoing below the surface. A demented laugh. The sound of a thousand hornet wings, and insect feet."
    girl "Hubo un grito profundo y desenfrenado que resonaba bajo la superficie. Una risa demente. El sonido de mil alas de avispas y pies de insectos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_fa3d1303:

    # girl "It grew closer. Climbing."
    girl "Se acercó más. Escalando."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bccf6ed5:

    # girl "As he stood, bodies were flung atop each other, as the demons and the forgotten built their tower to salvation."
    girl "Mientras él estaba de pie, los cuerpos fueron arrojados uno encima del otro, los demonios y los olvidados construyendo su torre hacia la salvación."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_787fdce8:

    # girl "“Who is He?” The Gravedigger asked. It was his turn to plead, but the corpses said nothing."
    girl "“¿Quin es Él?” Preguntó el Sepulturero. Era su turno de suplicar, pero los cadáveres no dijeron nada."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_768d5a1c:

    # girl "It didn’t take much for the Gravedigger to realize that they couldn’t respond even if they wanted to."
    girl "No le costó mucho al sepulturero darse cuenta de que no podrían responder aunque quisieran."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_3c64ac45:

    # girl "They didn’t know."
    girl "Ellos no lo sabían."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_88487ea3:

    # girl "As the Gravedigger ran home, the ghoul uttered a final mantra under her breath."
    girl "Mientras el Sepulturero corría a casa, el ghoul pronunció un mantra final en voz baja."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_0c3bf306:

    # girl "The words still tasted so alien to her, so vile and disgusting. It was all they had left."
    girl "Las palabras todavía le sabían tan ajenas, tan viles y repugnantes. Era todo lo que les quedaba."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:334
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_37d4cf66:

    # girl "“God must know that He is coming.”"
    girl "“Dios debe saber que Él viene.”"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:496
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ac660d1_3:

    # "They suddenly turn towards you. Their mouth turned up into a warm grin. Their eyes sinister."
    "De repente miran en tu dirección. Sus bocas forman en una cálida sonrisa. Sus ojos siniestros."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1503e9ec:

    # man "Here I lay, all snuggled up in bed, warm and satisfied under the soft silk covers, watching some stupid documentary on TV I’d never heard of."
    man "Aquí yacía, acurrucada en la cama, cálida y satisfecha bajo las suaves sábanas de seda, viendo un estúpido documental en la televisión del que nunca había oído hablar."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e1f7cf3e:

    # man "I’d turn it over, but the gallon tub of cookie dough ice cream wouldn’t let me use my hands for anything other than shoveling the frozen treat into my mouth."
    man "Le daría la vuelta, pero el bote de un galón de helado de masa para galletas no me dejaba usar mis manos para otra cosa que no fuera para meterme el dulce congelado en la boca."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_cb3e9bcd:

    # man "Nights like these are rare, it isn’t often that everyone’s out of the house but me, so I make sure to savour them, in fact, I wasn’t expecting anyone back till the morning."
    man "Noches como éstas son raras. No es frecuente que todos salgan de la casa menos yo, así que me aseguro de saborearlas. De hecho, no esperaba que nadie regresara hasta la mañana."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bef205f1:

    # man "That’s what made the sound of the door opening downstairs so alarming."
    man "Eso es lo que hizo que el sonido de la puerta al abrirse en la planta baja fuera tan alarmante."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_031dd710:

    # man "Panic hits me like a steam train, I silently leap out from under the covers, spilling the ice cream all over the pristine white carpet on the floor, and creak open the wardrobe next to the bed."
    man "El pánico me golpea como un tren. Salto silenciosamente de debajo de las mantas, derramo el helado por toda la alfombra blanca e inmaculada y abro el armario junto a la cama."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_78f96296:

    # man "I hear footsteps, heavy and indiscreet, like they want me to know they’re here."
    man "Escucho pasos, pesados ​​e indiscretos, como si quisieran que supiera que están aquí."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_396504ac:

    # man "I pant, and pick up the spoon I had just been using to enjoy a relaxing night."
    man "Pierdo el aliento ,y tomo la cuchara que acababa de usar para disfrutar de una noche relajante."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a2ad18cd:

    # man "The footsteps get louder, I force myself into the miniscule space remaining in the wardrobe, and close the door, just as the stranger opens the bedroom door, not sparing any seconds for silence."
    man "Los pasos se hacen más fuertes, me fuerzo a entrar en el minúsculo espacio que queda en el armario, y cierro la puerta, justo cuando el extraño abre la puerta del dormitorio, sin escatimar segundos para tener silencio."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_c53f3b79:

    # man "I peer through the gap, his face looks familiar, but I can’t place my finger on where I know him from."
    man "Miro a través del hueco, y su rostro me resulta familiar, pero no puedo señalar de dónde lo conozco."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_00484368:

    # man "He spots the spilled ice cream, and darts his head across the wide expanse of the bedroom."
    man "Ve el helado derramado y mueve la cabeza, contemplando la amplia extensión del dormitorio."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_82338b32:

    # man "“Hello?” he calls, not sounding vicious, but I’ve made that mistake before."
    man "“¿Hola?” él llama, sin sonar cruel, pero he comitod ese error antes."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_f709b382:

    # man "Never, under any circumstances, assume friendliness from a voice."
    man "Nunca, bajo ninguna circunstancia, asumas que una voz es amistosa."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_a9c18f42:

    # man "He looks under the bed. Oh crap, he’s looking for someone."
    man "Busca bajo la cama. Oh mierda, está buscando a alquien."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_1ac3ef21:

    # man "I hold back a whimper, and start bending the bowl of the spoon back and forth, hoping to snap it off and create some way of defending myself."
    man "Contengo un gemido y empiezo a doblar el cuenco de la cuchara hacia adelante y hacia atrás, con la esperanza de romperla y crear alguna forma de defenderme."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_93f0cbd4:

    # man "It snaps, but it creates a metallic click, the man turns his head around, and makes his way to the wardrobe, I’m shaking now."
    man "Se rompe, pero crea un clic metálico. El hombre gira la cabeza y se dirige al armario. Ahora estoy temblando."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_0160ed1a:

    # man "Please don’t open it, please don’t open it, please don’t open it!"
    man "¡Por favor no abras, por favor no abras, por favor no abras!"

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_bc7f11a1:

    # man "The door swings open, and he sees me, we scream simultaneously in fear and surprise."
    man "La puerta se abre, y él me ve. Gritamos a la vez del miedo y la sorpresa."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_33df57b9:

    # man "Without hesitation, I leap onto the man, and start digging into whatever stretch of flesh I can with the sharp edge of the spoon handle, he screeches in clear pain, but I won’t stop, I hammer the handle deep into his chest and neck, over and over, till he becomes motionless."
    man "Sin dudarlo, salto sobre el hombre y empiezo a escarbar en cualquier tramo de carne que pueda con el borde afilado del mango de la cuchara. Él chilla de dolor, pero no me detendré. Golpeo el mango profundamente en su pecho y cuello, una y otra vez, hasta que se queda inmóvil."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_020b5b72:

    # man "I’ve killed him."
    man "Lo he matado."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_6b1b13df:

    # man "I cry in disgust, and sprint downstairs and away from the house, I charge down the road until I feel like I’m far enough away."
    man "Dejo escapar un sonido de disgusto, y corro escaleras abajo, lejos de la casa. Corro por la carretera hasta que siento que estoy lo suficientemente lejos."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_dfc898f6:

    # man "I sit down for a moment, and exhale heavily before regaining my composure."
    man "Me siento por un momento y exhalo profundamente antes de recuperar la compostura."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:508
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_e817b734:

    # man "Pulling out my phone, I open social media and search #party, hopefully this time, I’ll find a household that isn’t lying when they say they’ll be out all night."
    man "Saco mi teléfono, abro las redes sociales y busco #fiesta. Con suerte, ésta vez, encontraré un hogar que no mienta cuando dicen que estarán fuera toda la noche."

# game/events/dreams/recurring_nightmare.rpy:558
translate spanish d_Recurring_Nightmare_1_part2_4ac660d1_4:

    # "They suddenly turn towards you. Their mouth turned up into a warm grin. Their eyes sinister."
    "De repente miran en tu dirección. Sus bocas forman en una cálida sonrisa. Sus ojos siniestros."

